<h5 class="title">contacting the studio:</h5>
<p>Please contact the studio by email. You may use either the form on this page or the link that appears at the bottom of each page of the site.</p>
<p>If this is an initial inquiry concerning a textile, include some information on the textile's history and environment if you can. If possible, attach photographs of the item and any areas of concern.</p>
<p>The studio will reply with suggestions appropriate to your situation. Most often, this will lead to a detailed examination of the item that produces a written treatment plan.</p>

<form id="contactForm" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <fieldset>
    <label for="name">name</label>
    <input placeholder="name" name="name" type="text" required>
    <label for="email">email</label>
    <input placeholder="name@email.net" name="email" type="email" required>
    <label for="body">message</label>
    <textarea placeholder="body of messageâ€¦" name="body" required></textarea>
    <label for="fileupload">attachments</label>
    <input id="fileupload" type="file" name="files" multiple><br>
    <input class="button-primary" value="Send" type="submit">
  </fieldset>
</form>

<script>
$("#contactForm").validate();
</script>
